Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "šon" in different forms and positions:

1. *Šon* sam stavio na vrata da ne udaraju o zid. (I put a doorstop* on the door so it doesn't hit the wall.)
2. Kupio sam novi *šon* za svoju torbu. (I bought a new shoulder strap* for my bag.)
3. Molim vas da *šonove* dobro pričvrstite da ne bi ispalo. (Please make sure to fasten the* screws* tightly so they don't fall out.)
4. Ova vrata nemaju *štok* ni *šon*, kako ih možemo pričvrstiti? (These doors don't have a* frame* or a* jamb*, how can we attach them?)
5. U poslednje vreme puno radim u *šonovima* i imam bolove u ramenima. (Lately, I've been working a lot in the* straps* and I have shoulder pain.)

I hope these sentences help illustrate the different uses and forms of the word "šon" in Serbian!